      CLIENT_PACKAGE 
      static java.lang.String CLIENT_PACKAGE
      Name of the XML tag you must provide in the Android manifest.
      public static final java.lang.String CLIENT_PACKAGE
      Name of the XML tag you must provide in the Android manifest. This string identifies the client and should be used as the client's provider authority. This string is also prepended to the notification Intent action strings, so that clients can intercept updates from the service and update the notification UI. Example snippet from your Android manifest: 
       
 <meta-data android:name="com.penthera.virtuososdk.client.pckg" android:value="com.penthera.reference.provider" />
      See Also:
      Common.Notifications, VirtuosoSDKContentProvider, Constant Field Values
      CONFIGURE_VIRTUOSO_SERVICE_LOGGING

      Intent action used to configure logging within Virtuoso.
      public static final java.lang.String CONFIGURE_VIRTUOSO_SERVICE_LOGGING
      Intent action used to configure logging within Virtuoso. A debug version of Virtuoso defaults to verbose logging; the release version defaults to having logging disabled. To change the log level, send EXTRA_VIRTUOSO_SERVICE_LOGLEVEL, specifying one of the values defined in Common.LogLevels.
